      "content": "You are absolutely right that Tylenol is safer for your stomach than ibuprofen, but taking it will only dull the pain without stopping the infection, which is dangerous if this is indeed appendicitis. Gas or period cramps do not typically cause nausea combined with pain that specifically migrates to the lower right side in such a sharp way. Please do not wait until work tomorrow; the only way to confirm it is not appendicitis is to get a blood test and ultrasound at the hospital now, as this condition can rupture and become fatal within 24 hours.",
